l passive: “You must obey the law.”','input','[]','the law must be obeyed','2025-05-30 17:47:39'),(319,91,'Turn into perfect passive: “Someone has stolen my wallet.”','input','[]','my wallet has been stolen','2025-05-30 17:47:39'),(320,92,'Which is the correct nominalisation of \"to decide\"?','multiple_choice','[\"decide\", \"decision\", \"deciding\", \"decisio\"]','decision','2025-05-30 17:48:35'),(321,92,'Which suffix makes a noun from \"to improve\"?','multiple_choice','[\"-tion\", \"-ment\", \"-ity\", \"-ance\"]','-ment','2025-05-30 17:48:35'),(322,92,'Which sentence uses nominalisation?','multiple_choice','[\"The investigation revealed new facts.\", \"They will investigate the case.\", \"We are investigating now.\", \"Investigate the case promptly.\"]','The investigation revealed new facts.','2025-05-30 17:48:35'),(323,92,'Which suffix applies to \"active\"?','multiple_choice','[\"activity\", \"activate\", \"activated\", \"activism\"]','activity','2025-05-30 17:48:35'),(324,92,'Choose the formal version of \"We need to finish the report.\"','multiple_choice','[\"Report completion is required.\", \"We finish the report.\", \"We have to finish the report.\", \"Finish the report, please.\"]','Report completion is required.','2025-05-30 17:48:35'),(325,92,'Which word is a nominalisation of \"perform\"?','multiple_choice','[\"perform\", \"performance\", \"performing\", \"performed\"]','performance','2025-05-30 17:48:35'),(326,92,'Which is a formal register tip?','multiple_choice','[\"Avoid contractions like “don\'t”\", \"Use slang for emphasis\", \"Write in first person always\", \"Use emoticons 😊\"]','Avoid contractions like “don\'t”','2025-05-30 17:48:35'),(327,92,'Nominalise the verb \"to create\".','input','[]','creation','2025-05-30 17:48:35'),(328,92,'Nominalise the adjective \"accurate\".','input','[]','accuracy','2025-05-30 17:48:35'),(329,92,'Convert to nominalisation: “They will evaluate the results.”','input','[]','an evaluation of the results will be made','2025-05-30 17:48:35'),(330,92,'Convert to formal: “We need to improve performance.”','input','[]','performance improvement is necessary','2025-05-30 17:48:35'),(331,92,'Nominalise the verb \"to organise\".','input','[]','organisation','2025-05-30 17:48:35'),(332,92,'Convert to formal from: “He helped me.”','input','[]','his assistance was valuable','2025-05-30 17:48:35'),(333,92,'Write a nominalised sentence: “She suggested we postpone the meeting.”','input','[]','her suggestion led to the postponement of the meeting','2025-05-30 17:48:35'),(334,93,'Which word is an additive discourse marker?','multiple_choice','[\"however\", \"moreover\", \"although\", \"despite\"]','moreover','2025-05-30 17:49:32'),(335,93,'Which marker indicates contrast?','multiple_choice','[\"therefore\", \"moreover\", \"on the other hand\", \"firstly\"]','on the other hand','2025-05-30 17:49:32'),(336,93,'Which marker shows a result?','multiple_choice','[\"because\", \"although\", \"thus\", \"nevertheless\"]','thus','2025-05-30 17:49:32'),(337,93,'Which word is a causal connector?','multiple_choice','[\"in addition\", \"however\", \"because\", \"furthermore\"]','because','2025-05-30 17:49:32'),(338,93,'Which is a concession marker?','multiple_choice','[\"nevertheless\", \"moreover\", \"firstly\", \"therefore\"]','nevertheless','2025-05-30 17:49:32'),(339,93,'Which marker is used to sequence points?','multiple_choice','[\"because\", \"firstly\", \"however\", \"too\"]','firstly','2025-05-30 17:49:32'),(340,93,'Which marker adds extra information?','multiple_choice','[\"despite\", \"also\", \"when\", \"so\"]','also','2025-05-30 17:49:32'),(341,93,'Translate to English: \"Более того\".','input','[]','moreover','2025-05-30 17:49:32'),(342,93,'Fill in the blank: \"____, the results were inconclusive.\"','input','[]','nevertheless','2025-05-30 17:49:32'),(343,93,'Translate: \"Однако, это было сложно.\"','input','[]','however, it was difficult','2025-05-30 17:49:32'),(344,93,'Translate to English: \"Таким образом\".','input','[]','thus','2025-05-30 17:49:32'),(345,93,'Fill in the blank: \"____ he studied hard, he passed.\"','input','[]','because','2025-05-30 17:49:32'),(346,93,'Fill in the blank: \"____, we will discuss the findings.\"','input','[]','firstly','2025-05-30 17:49:32'),(347,93,'Translate: \"В результате\".','input','[]','as a result','2025-05-30 17:49:32'),(348,94,'What does \"to hit the nail on the head\" mean?','multiple_choice','[\"to be exactly right\", \"to make a mistake\", \"to hit someone\", \"to build something\"]','to be exactly right','2025-05-30 17:50:58'),(349,94,'Which is a correct collocation?','multiple_choice','[\"make a decision\", \"do a decision\", \"take a decision\", \"have a decision\"]','make a decision','2025-05-30 17:50:58'),(350,94,'Is \"turn off the lights\" separable or inseparable?','multiple_choice','[\"separable\", \"inseparable\", \"both\", \"none\"]','separable','2025-05-30 17:50:58'),(351,94,'Which is an informal alternative to \"deal with\"?','multiple_choice','[\"deal with\", \"address\", \"manage\", \"tackle\"]','deal with','2025-05-30 17:50:58'),(352,94,'What does \"spill the beans\" mean?','multiple_choice','[\"to reveal a secret\", \"to eat beans\", \"to cause trouble\", \"to miss the point\"]','to reveal a secret','2025-05-30 17:50:58'),(353,94,'Which collocation is correct?','multiple_choice','[\"take a chance\", \"make a chance\", \"do a chance\", \"give a chance\"]','take a chance','2025-05-30 17:50:58'),(354,94,'Which phrasal verb is inseparable?','multiple_choice','[\"turn on\", \"look after\", \"turn off\", \"turn up\"]','look after','2025-05-30 17:50:58'),(355,94,'Translate into English: \"решить проблему\" using natural collocation.','input','[]','to address the problem','2025-05-30 17:50:58'),(356,94,'Provide a synonym for \"call it a day\".','input','[]','to stop working','2025-05-30 17:50:58'),(357,94,'Fill in the blank: \"Don’t ______ the beans!\"','input','[]','spill','2025-05-30 17:50:58'),(358,94,'Translate: \"принять решение\".','input','[]','make a decision','2025-05-30 17:50:58'),(359,94,'Use a phrasal verb: \"уведомлять кого-то\" (inform someone).','input','[]','let someone know','2025-05-30 17:50:58'),(360,94,'Translate idiom: \"pay attention\".','input','[]','pay attention','2025-05-30 17:50:58'),(361,94,'Convert to formal: replace \"deal with\" in “We need to deal with this issue.”','input','[]','we need to address this issue','2025-05-30 17:50:58');
